AI-Based Password Strength Checker Using Machine Learning

Abstract

In the modern digital era, passwords play a vital role in protecting personal and organizational information. Weak passwords can easily be guessed or cracked, leading to unauthorized access and security breaches. The purpose of this project is to develop an AI-Based Password Strength Checker using Machine Learning techniques. The system evaluates password strength by analyzing different features such as password length, uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters. Based on these features, a trained Machine Learning model predicts whether a password is Weak, Medium, or Strong. The project helps users create stronger passwords and promotes cybersecurity awareness.

Introduction

Cybersecurity has become one of the most important concerns in today's digital world. Almost every online platform requires users to create passwords to secure their accounts and personal information. However, many users choose simple and predictable passwords, making their accounts vulnerable to hacking attempts.

Traditional password validation methods mainly rely on predefined rules and often fail to provide intelligent feedback. Machine Learning offers a more advanced solution by learning patterns from data and making predictions based on password characteristics. This project combines Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to create a web-based password strength evaluation system.

Problem Statement

Weak passwords remain one of the primary causes of cybersecurity incidents. Users frequently create passwords that are easy to remember but also easy to crack. Existing systems may only check basic requirements and do not provide detailed analysis or recommendations. Therefore, there is a need for an intelligent system capable of evaluating password strength and guiding users toward better password creation practices.

Objectives

The main objectives of this project are:

1. To develop an AI-based password strength evaluation system.
2. To classify passwords into Weak, Medium, and Strong categories.
3. To provide recommendations for improving password security.
4. To increase awareness about secure password practices.
5. To demonstrate the practical application of Machine Learning in cybersecurity.

