Methodology

Data Collection

A dataset containing password-related information was prepared. The dataset included password characteristics such as length, uppercase letters, lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters along with corresponding strength labels.

Feature Extraction

When a user enters a password, the system extracts several features, including:

- Password Length
- Number of Uppercase Letters
- Number of Lowercase Letters
- Number of Digits
- Number of Special Characters

These features serve as input for the Machine Learning model.

Model Training

The Random Forest Classifier algorithm was selected because of its efficiency, accuracy, and reliability in classification tasks. The model was trained using the prepared dataset and then saved for future predictions.

Prediction Process

When a user enters a new password, the system extracts its features and sends them to the trained model. The model predicts the strength category and returns the result along with recommendations.

